history.content:
Can students enroll in 160 and other courses with time conflicts? (There's a 30 minute overlap on one of the days with a requirement for my other major, and I don't think it'll be the biggest problem during the semester in terms of missed content, etc. But I'm assuming that it will make CalCentral upset when I'm trying to sign up for classes.)

Also does 160 require lecture attendance/track attendance in any way?
history.subject: Enrolling in 160 with Time-Conflict
